body.headline: Apple Unveils Metal 4 at WWDC 2025 - AI-Powered Graphics Revolution
body.summary: Apple introduced Metal 4 with native AI capabilities enabling Mac developers to run AI computations locally on GPU.
body.fullText: At WWDC 2025, Apple launched Metal 4, a graphics API with built-in AI features allowing Mac applications to perform AI tasks on GPU without relying on cloud services. This innovation enhances performance and privacy, enabling native Mac apps to compete with NVIDIA CUDA systems for AI workloads, potentially shifting AI development back to local applications.
